methods.and:
Return the logical and of two bitmaps as a new bitmap. This is equivalent to the intersection of the two bitmaps
 as sets.

:param b1: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.impl.rsp.RspBitmap) - a bitmap
:param b2: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.impl.rsp.RspBitmap) - a bitmap
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.impl.rsp.RspBitmap) b1 and b2 as a new bitmap.
methods.andEquals:
Removes every element from this bitmap that is not in the other bitmap.

:param other: io.deephaven.engine.rowset.impl.rsp.RspBitmap
:return: io.deephaven.engine.rowset.impl.rsp.RspBitmap
methods.andNot:
Return the logical result of r1 and not r2 as a new bitmap. This is equivalent to removing every element in b2
 from b1. The arguments won't be modified.

:param b1: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.impl.rsp.RspBitmap) - a bitmap
:param b2: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.impl.rsp.RspBitmap) - a bitmap
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.impl.rsp.RspBitmap) b1 and not b2 as a new bitmap.
